{{pov|date=September 2018}}

[[File:Womanpower_logo.jpg|alt=feminist symbol|thumb|150px|[[Political colour#Purple|Purple]] has historically represented feminism.]]

'''Purplewashing''' is a [[compound word]] modelled on the term ''[[whitewash]]''. In the context of [[feminism]], it is used to describe a variety of [[Politics|political]] and [[marketing]] strategies aimed at promoting countries, people, companies and other organisations through an appeal to [[gender equality]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.elconfidencial.com/cultura/2016-04-03/del-pornoburka-al-purplewashing-los-trucos-mas-sucios-contra-el-feminismo_1170764/|title=Del pornoburka al purplewashing, los trucos más sucios contra el feminismo|last=|first=|date=|work=El Confidencial|access-date=|language=spanish}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.centredelas.org/images/INFORMES_i_altres_PDF/informe30_eng.pdf|title=Gender and Military Culture|last=|first=|date=|website=Centre Delás|format=pdf|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>

The term is commonly used to denounce the use of feminism to justify what is perceived as [[xenophobic]] or [[Islamophobia|Islamophobic]] policies.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/07/14/world/europe/14burqa.html|title=Parliament Moves France Closer to a Ban on Facial Veils|last=|first=|date=|work=the New York Times|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.pikaramagazine.com/2014/12/velo-integral-el-feminismo-como-exclusion/|title=Burkas en el ojo ajeno: el feminismo como exclusión|last=|first=|date=|work=Pikara Magazine|access-date=|language=spanish}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.eldiario.es/zonacritica/burkini-barbijaputa-purple_washing_6_553004709.html|title='Purple washing' o acordarse del feminismo cuando interesa|last=|first=|date=|work=eldiario|access-date=|language=spanish}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.pikaramagazine.com/2014/12/velo-integral-el-feminismo-como-exclusion/|title=Burkas en el ojo ajeno: el feminismo como exclusión|last=|first=|date=|work=Pikara Magazine|access-date=|language=spanish}}</ref>

The word is also used to criticise how [[Western countries]], that have not achieved complete gender equality, justify this by pointing out that other countries (often majority [[muslim]]) or cultures still have a worse [[quality of life]] for women.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://electronicintifada.net/blogs/sarah-irving/australian-labor-party-spins-israels-occupation-feminist|title=Australian Labor Party spins Israel’s occupation as feminist|last=|first=|date=|work=Electronic Intfada|access-date=}}</ref>

